cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics): The paper focuses on learning the inverse kinematics of a musculoskeletal robot arm using motor babbling and proposes a local online motor babbling approach. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper uses directed goal babbling and Covariance Matrix Adaptation Evolution Strategy (CMA-ES) for learning the inverse kinematics and exploring motor abundance. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a learning approach for a highly redundant system using motor babbling and heuristics to define the goal space. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision): Although not directly related to computer vision, the paper may involve some visual feedback for the robot arm during the learning process. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper deals with learning the inverse kinematics of a musculoskeletal robot arm, which falls under the domain of systems and control.
